climbs.name: Swingers
climbs.fa: Rupesh Chhagan, bb Kirk Jones and Marisa Hinton

content.description: Bolt 1 is at the bottom right of a large guitar-pick shaped flake.  The flake edge is along the bottom, left and top. The guitar pick points up and right.  The bottom of the pick is a diagonal formation completing the pick.  The anchors are up and left from the last bolt.
content.location: To the right of Check Your Head on the guitar-pick formation.

content.description: Instead of using the arete to finish, use the arete to clip the bolt, then move left out onto the face and finish straight up above the bolt.  This was Scott's original style for the route.
content.location: Far right side of Check Your Head Wall.

content.description: 5.3 climbing to the high Bolt 1.  Bolt 2 is at 11 o'clock.  Bolt 2 doesn't protect falls back onto the ramp and Bolt 3 has no good clip stance. Probably mid 5.12. Limestoner has it as 11+.  Pass up a stick clip for Bolt 3 is best.
content.location: First route on the left on Check Your Head Wall.

content.description: Tall route.  At the last bolt, use the arete to clip and climb up the arete to the anchors.
content.location: Far right side of Check Your Head Wall.  16 paces to the left of Crack Attack on Insect Wall (including Block Party).

content.description: To the right of Chop Suey Style.  Runout over a clean fall.  Bolt 1 is above a diagonal left-leaning "crack".  Bolt 3 is up and far left.
content.location: To the right of Chop Suey Style on Check Your Head Wall.

content.description: Hike carefully under a 6' tall boulder and watch your head so it doesn't get bashed!  After Mai Tai Wall and before Insect Wall (including Block Party).
